        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Leipzig</placeName>
                    <date>Jan 29. 1873.</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Again I trouble you   A new edition of the Expression of the Emotions is to be done<ref target="#foot.f1"/>   So I beg to ask you, if you have anything to add or to alter or if you have in any way a particular wish.</p>
<p>There is a litterary notice, which I thought you might like to get. You mention that “Gratiolet remarks, whenever our attention is long concentrated on any subject we forget to breathe” (Expression, p 179).<ref target="#foot.f2"/> May I draw your attention (without interrupting your breathing) to an article of <hi rend="underline">Nasse</hi> in Meckel’s Deutsches Archiv für Physiologie, Bd. 2. 1816. p. 1. “on the want of respiration during mental occupations”, which contains some observations of great interest, stating the same as Gratiolet.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>Hoping that your health may be pretty good I remain | Ever yours sincerely | J. Victor Carus</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="annotations">
                <note><hi rend="italic">Bottom of first page</hi>: <hi rend="italic">two crosses pencil</hi>; ‘77QQQQ 13’ <hi rend="italic">pencil</hi></note>
            </div>

            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Carus’s last letter to CD was that of 21 January 1873. Carus had translated <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref> into German (Carus trans. 1872); a second German edition was published in 1874 (Carus trans. 1874).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD cited <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1953.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Louis Pierre Gratiolet</ref> and <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2994.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Gratiolet [1865]</ref>, p. 232.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">In <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2401.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi> 2d ed.</ref>, p. 187, Carus is credited with the reference to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_6422.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Christian Friedrich Nasse</ref> and <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_5790.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Nasse 1816</ref>. The <hi rend="italic">Deutsches Archiv für die Physiologie</hi> was edited by <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_6311.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Johann Friedrich Meckel</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
